/*------------------------------------------------------------------ 
 MBlue Nav-Style Buttons Vista (Ver. 0.4.0)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Author: M.BLUE - Tested on: Firefox 3.0.5 - Last Update: 27.01.2009
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Description:
 1. Transforms the TOOLBARBUTTONS and make it like the
    NAV-BUTTONS: same blue background and dropmarker.
 2. Can use Separator/Spacer to customize the buttons (read below).
 3. Supports SMALL and BIG ICONS.
 4. Integrates with "Combine Nav-Buttons Vista".
 5. Integrates with the other Nav-Style styles.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Notes:
-Using other Styles/Extensions/Themes may change some margin/border
 settings, making the buttons not aligned.
 If so, try not using other styles that changes margins in the
 nav-bar, and use the default firefox theme. 

-Some Ext. Icons (like Download Helper) will not work correctly.

-Works in the Nav-Bar only.

-Even if this style supports big icons, it works better with small
 ones, because the default big icons are too big to fit inside the
 buttons, so this style resizes them.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Customize the Buttons:
 This style uses the Toolbar-Separator to add the L/R part of the
 button-image, and the Toolbar-Spacer to create the 2px margin
 between the buttons, and other stuff. Open the customize window,
 and follow these guidelines to place the items:

 Separator [RED]: Place this at LEFT/RIGHT side of any buttons to
                  create the rounded edge.

 Spacer [GREEN]:  Place this next to a separator to adjust it.
                  Place this between 2 buttons to create the 2px
                  margin like the Nav-Buttons.

 Other Icons:     Place the icons with nothing in-between to make
                  them unite.
                  Icons with the dropmarker doesn't need the
                  separator on the right side.

 Example:

 [URLBAR] [GREEN] [RED] [ICON] [ICON] [GREEN] [ICON] [RED] [GREEN]

 This makes the first 2 Icons united, then 2px margin, and then the
 third Icon, all of this is inside a rounded blue box similar to
 the Nav-Buttons.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Customize the Bookmarks:
 If you use the Bookmarks inside the nav-bar you should:

 1) Edit your bookmarks, add a separator before and after all
    your bookmarks links/folders (this makes the rounded edges).
 2) You can place a separator between icons to create a space (with
    rounded edges on before and after icons).
 3) Try keeping your bookmarks-bar small (less links, use folders!)
    or the bar will overlap other icons in the nav-bar.

 Example:

 [SEP] [FOLDER] [FOLDER] [FOLDER] [SEP] [LINK] [LINK] [SEP]

 This makes the first 3 folders inside a rounded box, then space,
 and then another 2 links inside a rounded box.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
OTHER CUSTOMIZING OPTIONS:
 1. BUTTONS OPACITY.
 2. BOOKMARKS TEXT REMOVE/SETTINGS.

> GO TO BOTTOM OF THE PAGE TO CUSTOMIZE
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Supported Extensions:
 Works with all the default buttons, and should support almost all
 additional extensions buttons.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Integrates with:
 MBlue Combine Nav-Buttons Vista
 MBlue Nav-Style Url-Bar Vista
>MBlue Nav-Style Buttons Vista
